@node BENTH "Benthic Behemoth"

@{b}Benthic Behemoth@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = TP(R)
Type    = Summon Serpent (7/6)
Cost    = 5UUU
Artist  = Jim Nelson

Text(TP): Islandwalk (If defending player controls any islands, this
          creature unblockable.)

Flavor Text: @{i}"Deep devourer concealed in darkhome Shrouded it seeks all
               becomes fodder Once will swam alone and asea But no more."
               ---Rootwater Saga@{ui}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode

@node CAPSI "Capsize"

@{b}Capsize@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = TP(C)
Type    = Instant
Cost    = 1UU
Artist  = Tom Wanerstrand

Text(TP): Buyback 3 (You may pay an additional 3 when you play this spell.
          If you do, put it into your hand instead of your graveyard as part of
          the spell's effect.)
          Return target permanent to owner's hand.

Flavor Text: @{i}No Flavor Text@{ui}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode

@node CHILL "Chill"

@{b}Chill@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = TP(U)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 1U
Artist  = Greg Simanson

Text(TP): Red spells cost an additional 2 to play.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Temper, temper." ---Ertai, wizard adept@{ui}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode

@node COUNT "Counterspell"


@node DISMI "Dismiss"

@{b}Dismiss@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = TP(U)
Type    = Interrupt
Cost    = 2UU
Artist  = Donato Giancola

Text(TP): Counter target spell. 
          Draw a card.

Flavor Text: @{i}"There is nothing you can do that I cannot simply deny."
               ---Ertai, wizard adept@{ui}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node DUPLI "Duplicity"

@{b}Duplicity@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = TP(R)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 3UU
Artist  = Dan Frazier

Text(TP): When Duplicity comes into play, put the top five cards of your
          library face down on Duplicity.
          During your upkeep, you may exchange all the cards in your
          hand for the cards on Duplicity.
          At the end of your turn, choose and discard a card.
          If you lose control of Duplicity, put all cards on it into owner's
          graveyard.

Flavor Text: @{i}No Flavor Text@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_D.guide/DUPLI}

@endnode

@node ERMED "Ertai's Meddling" 

@{b}Ertai's Meddling @{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = TP(R)
Type    = Interrupt
Cost    = XU
Artist  = Steve Luke

Text(TP): When target spell is successfully cast, put X delay counters on 
          it. X cannot be 0.
          During each upkeep of that spell's caster, remove a delay counter 
          from the spell. If the spell has no delay counters on it, it resolves.

Flavor Text: @{i}No Flavor Text@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_E.guide/ERMED}

@endnode

@node ESSHA "Escaped Shapeshifter"

@{b}Escaped Shapeshifter@{ub}

Color   = Blue
Rarity  = TP(R)
Type    = Summon Shapeshifter (3/4)
Cost    = 3UU
Artist  = Douglas Shuler

Text(TP): As long as your opponent controls any creatures with flying, 
          Escaped Shapeshifter gains flying. The same is true for first 
          strike, trample, and protection from any color.

Flavor Text: @{i}No Flavor Text@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_E.guide/ESHAP}

@endnode

